headline: Co-Chiefs Greg Peters and Ted Sarandos Have Made Netflix More Nimble
summary: Netflix   is the king of media.  Last year, in an entertainment industry devoid of growth, the company’s revenue rose 16%, to $39 billion, with free-cash-flow generation of $6.9 billion.  Netflix is nimble, and now willing to experiment with things it once vowed never to do.

headline: Netflix receives Street-high target at Pivotal Research
summary: Investing.com -- Pivotal Research lifted its price target on Netflix (NASDAQ:NFLX) shares to $1,600, the highest on Wall Street, citing greater confidence in the company’s long-term market position and stronger valuation metrics.

headline: Could Netflix become an aggregator of linear channels?
summary: Investing.com -- Netflix’s new partnership with French broadcaster Television Francaise 1 SA (EPA:TFFP) to carry live content on its platform has sparked speculation about the company’s potential role as an aggregator of linear channels.
